                       "message":  "SCENE-OPEN-WIRING: in-app Ctrl+O scene Open + GLB watcher teardown\n\nWire Ctrl+O to open a .rge-scene / .rge-project from inside the running editor. The binary-owned SceneOpenHook loads the path into a fresh kernel World (via rge_scene_loader::load_scene_world_from_path) and handle_open_request swaps it in live through EditorShell::replace_world. .glb keeps its existing render-swap path. The scene load runs in the hook BEFORE the swap, so a malformed scene leaves the live world untouched (the scene analogue of the GLB commit-after-success property).\n\nAfter a scene Open clears glb_source_path, the binary-owned GLB watcher is torn down via a new GlbWatcherAction::Teardown, closing the watcher-shutdown caveat carried through #263/#264/#265.\n\neditor-shell stays dependency-clean (no rge-scene-loader / rge-data / rfd / notify): the scene loader, dialog, and watcher all stay binary-owned behind trait objects, mirroring the GLB hook split. The dialog gains an All Files filter so a literal .rge-project is pickable in v0.\n\nTests: +6 headless editor-shell scene-open tests (swap+source-clear, failure no-op, unsupported no-op, missing-hook no-op, PIE gate, hook-survives-swap); the 4 watcher-decision unit tests move to the GlbWatcherAction enum and a 5th teardown case is added.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
